			<h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900">
				Run a validator for {{chainName}} staking
			</h2>
			<p class="my-2">Stakers.space guide works with a concept of validator instances. You are used to have only one validator service from the other staking guides. However, this one service is just a single instance. This guide supports you to set multiple such validator instances on a single machine (if necessary), which has following benefits:</p>
			<ul class="list-disc my-4 pl-6">
				<li>You are able to keep validators separated - e.g. based on used deposit / withdrawal / fee recipient wallet address</li>
				<li>Keep logs in smaller size</li>
				<li>Remove a limitation of thread perofmance - with more instances you are able to you your CPU and threads in a more efficient way that results in option to run more validators on a single machine.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Under 1 validator instance you can run 1 as well as hundreds of validators. We did numerous tests of efficient number of validators per instances and number of instances on a single machine. We can share this experience under a paid serice.</p>

			<span class="mt-10 mb-3 inline-flex items-center text-white text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">
				<span class="rounded-l-full bg-emerald-600 px-3 py-1 shadow">
					Validator
				</span>
				<span class="rounded-r-full bg-gray-300 text-gray-800 px-3 py-1 shadow">
					Keys
				</span>
			</span>
			<h3 class="text-md">Validator keys</h3>
			<p>To configurate an instance of validator service, you need at least one keystore. 1 keystore represents 1 validator. You can generate keystores on an <a href="">offline PC</a> with Validator Data generator tool, <a href="">see the guide</a>.</p>
			<ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-4">
				<li>
					<h4 class="mt-4">Get Keystores</h4>
					<p>Keystores can be generated with <a href="/{{chainUrl}}/keystores">validator keys generation guide</a>.</p>
					<p>The tool generates a directory <code>deposit_keys</code> with keystore json files and 1 deposit json file.</p>
					<a href="/{{chainUrl}}/keystores#generate"
						class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-black text-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-black">
